   <!--Project description-->
   <div class="desccontainer">
       <div class="desctext">
           <p>
               <b>Cryptocurrency</b> (noun): any form of currency that only exists digitally,
               that usually has no central issuing or regulating authority but instead uses a
               decentralized system to record transactions and manage the issuance of new units,
               and that relies on cryptography to prevent counterfeiting and fraudulent transactions.
               - <a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/cryptocurrency">Marriam-Webster dictionary</a>
               </br></br>
               My Cryptocurrency mine was started in late January of 2018.
               It was an initiative on me and my father's part to build infrastructure for a technology that revolutionizes the way value is exchanged.
               Using readily available computer parts, the work was completed in March of 2018.
               This project is ongoing because from time to time our mine needs repairs, and occasionally we change the coin that we are mining.
               Although we do not mine Bitcoin, the coins that we mine are based off of the same fundamentals originally proposed by Satoshi Nakamoto.
               </br></br>
               Our mine consists of 3 main computers with the follow hardware specifications:
               </br>
               <ol>
                   <li>16 GB of ram, 128 GB SSD (solid state drive), 12x Nvidia GTX 1080 ti, 1x Nvidia GTX 1070 ti</li>
                   <li>16 GB of ram, 250 GB SSD, 1x Nvidia GTX 1080 ti, 5x Nvidia GTX 1070 ti, 5x Nvidia GTX 1070</li>
                   <li>16 GB of ram, 8 GB USB flash drive, 1x Nvidia GTX 1080 ti</li>
               </ol>
               Due to hardware and software limitations, each computer has a limit of 13 graphics cards.
               The third computer is used to diagnose hardware problems that we occasionally have due to the amount of different parts in the other two computers.
               </br></br>
               We manage our computers using a service known as <a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://hiveos.farm">Hive OS</a>: a lightweight operating system that allows for remote control.
               We chose Hive OS because it is free and is a powerful utility for troubleshooting and adjusting settings on our computers.
               </br></br>
               Due to the heat generated by our mine, we installed 2 hydroponic fans with a duct leading outside.
               In the winter, we pull cold air in from outside to cool the room, and in the summer, we push hot air out of the room to cool the room.
               This cooling solution is cheap and allows us to cycle a lot of air.
               </br></br>
               This video serves as a virtual tour of our mining setup:
               </br></br>
               <p style="text-align:center;"><iframe width="756" height="426" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/wsNzEUod_aY" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
               </br></br>
               If you would like to learn about Cryptocurrency and Blockchain, here are a few resources that I recommend you start with:
               <ul>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.coindesk.com/information/what-is-blockchain-technology/">What is Blockchain Technology?</a></li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SSo_EIwHSd4">How Does Blockchain a Work?</a></li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://bitcoin.org/en/">Bitcoin Foundation Website</a></li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf  ">The Original Bitcoin Whitepaper</a></li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GmOzih6I1zs">What is Bitcoin Mining?</a></li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://coinmarketcap.com">CoinMarketCap</a> - Live Cryptocurrency prices</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.coinbase.com">Coinbase</a> - An easy way to buy and sell Cryptocurrency</li>
               </ul>
           </p>
